{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GnustoEngine"}],"title":"Frequently Asked Questions","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GnustoEngine\/documentation\/GnustoEngine\/FAQs"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"What-is-Gnusto","text":"What is Gnusto?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gnusto is a modern, open-source interactive fiction engine that provides a declarative approach to creating parser-based text adventures."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"gnusto-faqs.png","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You write games using Gnusto’s declarative DSL (domain-specific language), which is both intuitive and easy to work with, especially with code completion."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, because Gnusto-based games are written in Swift, you have the full power and potential of a fast, safe, general-purpose language standing by whenever you need it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Gnusto engine emphasizes type safety, testability, and a structured state-change pipeline that prevents common IF programming bugs."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Repository","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Documentation"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/samadhibot.github.io\/Gnusto\/documentation\/gnustoengine\/"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"License","type":"text"}]},{"text":": MIT (open source, commercial-friendly)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Can-I-see-it-in-action","text":"Can I see it in action?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes! You can try out Gnusto with just a few terminal commands.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following examples assume that you have Swift 6.2 or higher on your machine. If you don’t, please follow the instructions at "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" before you go on.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Play-the-example-games","text":"Play the example games","type":"heading"},{"code":["# Clone and explore","git clone https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto.git","cd Gnusto","","# Play the Cloak of Darkness demo","swift run CloakOfDarkness","","# Try the Zork 1 port (work in progress)","swift run Zork1"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Create-a-game-of-your-own","text":"Create a game of your own","type":"heading"},{"code":["# Run the bootstrap script from Github:","bash <(curl -sSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto\/refs\/heads\/main\/Scripts\/bootstrap)","","# Or, clone the repo and run the bootstrap script locally:","git clone https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto.git",".\/Gnusto\/Scripts\/bootstrap"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/asciinema.org\/a\/746386","isActive":true}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Why-would-I-choose-Gnusto-over-established-systems-like-Inform-7-or-TADS","text":"Why would I choose Gnusto over established systems like Inform 7 or TADS?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Gnusto takes a different approach: it’s built as a Swift library rather than as its own language, offering different trade-offs than established IF systems.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inform 7, TADS, and other traditional systems are mature, feature-rich, and have served the IF community brilliantly for decades. They offer extensive libraries, robust tooling, and thriving communities. Gnusto doesn’t try to replace them – instead, it explores what becomes possible when you build IF tooling on top of a modern, general-purpose programming language.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This approach means:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Full Language Access"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": You have all of Swift’s capabilities immediately available – no need to work around language limitations or wait for features to be added","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ecosystem Integration","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Leverage the entire Swift package ecosystem, or embed Gnusto as a component in larger applications","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Modern Development Practices","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Native support for testing frameworks, type safety, IDE tooling (Xcode, VS Code, Zed, Neovim, etc.), and debugging","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Flexible Architecture"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Gnusto can be a small part of another project, packaged in different ways, or extended through standard Swift patterns","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The trade-off is that Gnusto lacks the maturity, community resources, and extensions that established systems provide. It’s best suited for authors comfortable with programming who want the flexibility of a general-purpose language, or those interested in integrating IF into other Swift projects."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-do-I-write-games-in-Gnusto","text":"How do I write games in Gnusto?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"You define your game world declaratively using Gnusto’s declarative DSL, then add dynamic behaviors through event handlers.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s a minimal example:"}]},{"code":["\/\/ Define a location","let foyer = Location(.foyer)","    .name(\"Foyer of the Opera House\")","    .description(","        \"\"\"","        You are standing in a spacious hall, splendidly decorated in red","        and gold, with glittering chandeliers overhead. The entrance from","        the street is to the north, and there are doorways south and west.","        \"\"\"","    )","    .south(.bar)","    .west(.cloakroom)","    .north(","        blocked: \"\"\"","            You've only just arrived, and besides, the weather outside","            seems to be getting worse.","            \"\"\"","    )","    .inherentlyLit","","\/\/ Define an item","let cloak = Item(.cloak)","    .name(\"velvet cloak\")","    .description(","        \"\"\"","        A handsome cloak, of velvet trimmed with satin, and slightly","        spattered with raindrops. Its blackness is so deep that it","        almost seems to suck light from the room.","        \"\"\"","    )","    .adjectives(\"handsome\", \"dark\", \"black\", \"velvet\", \"satin\")","    .in(.player)","    .isTakable","    .isWearable","    .isWorn","","\/\/ Add dynamic behavior","let cloakHandler = ItemEventHandler(for: .cloak) {","    before(.drop, .insert) { context, _ in","        guard await context.player.location == .cloakroom else {","            throw ActionResponse.feedback(","                \"This isn't the best place to leave a smart cloak lying around.\"","            )","        }","        return nil","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Gnusto auto-wiring tool automatically discovers your content and generates the necessary boilerplate, so you focus on game design rather than plumbing.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"What-platforms-does-Gnusto-support","text":"What platforms does Gnusto support?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Gnusto runs on macOS, Linux, and Windows today, with mobile and web platforms planned.","type":"text"}]}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Development"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Distribution"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Status"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully supported"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Linux","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✅","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully supported (Ubuntu 24.04 tested)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Windows"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✅","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✅","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully supported (may need to disable SwiftLint)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✖️","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🏗️","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Planned (Swift runs natively)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Android","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✖️"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🏗️"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Planned (via Swift for Android)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Web"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✖️"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🔬"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Experimental (via WebAssembly)"}]}]]]},{"level":2,"anchor":"What-development-tools-do-I-need","text":"What development tools do I need?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need the Swift 6.2 toolchain and a text editor – everything else is included."}]}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Required"}]},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/download\/"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Recommended IDEs"}]},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/xcode\/"},{"type":"text","text":" (macOS only, best experience)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/"},{"type":"text","text":" with Swift extension (all platforms)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/zed.dev\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (fast, modern, great Swift support)"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Build System"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Swift Package Manager (included with Swift)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-capable-is-the-parser","text":"How capable is the parser?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The parser handles natural language input with support for complex commands, synonyms, and contextual understanding.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in capabilities:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"80+ standard verbs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (examine, take, drop, open, close, light, attack, etc.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex commands"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" (“put the brass lamp in the trophy case”)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pronouns","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (“examine table” then “put lamp on it”)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple objects"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (“take lamp and sword”)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Disambiguation","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" (“which key do you mean, the brass key or the iron key?”)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Synonyms and adjectives","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" (customizable per game)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The parser is extensible – you can add new verbs, modify syntax rules, or customize responses through the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GnustoEngine\/documentation\/GnustoEngine\/StandardMessenger"},{"type":"text","text":" system."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Can-I-import-my-existing-InformTADSDialog-game","text":"Can I import my existing Inform\/TADS\/Dialog game?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No, Gnusto doesn’t support importing from or exporting to other IF systems.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a deliberate design choice to avoid the complexity of format conversion and to leverage Swift’s native capabilities fully. To port an existing game, you’d need to recreate it using Gnusto’s DSL, though the declarative syntax makes this relatively straightforward."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-does-saving-and-restoring-work","text":"How does saving and restoring work?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Games are saved as JSON snapshots of the complete game state, making saves portable and human-readable."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The save system captures:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Player location and inventory","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All item states and positions","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Game flags and variables","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Score and turn count"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Active daemons and fuses"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note: The save format may change during beta as we gather feedback on compatibility needs."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Is-there-support-for-multimedia-graphics-sound","text":"Is there support for multimedia (graphics, sound)?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Not yet. Gnusto currently focuses on text-only experiences."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The architecture is designed to support multimedia extensions in the future, but the initial release concentrates on getting the core parser and world model right. The I\/O system is abstracted to allow for different presentation layers as the engine matures."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-do-I-handle-NPCs-and-dialogue","text":"How do I handle NPCs and dialogue?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gnusto provides basic NPC support through the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GnustoEngine\/documentation\/GnustoEngine\/CharacterSheet"},{"type":"text","text":" system. Conversation handling is on the roadmap."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"code":["let thief = Item(.thief)","    .name(\"thief\")","    .synonyms(\"thief\", \"robber\", \"man\", \"person\")","    .adjectives(\"shady\", \"suspicious\", \"seedy\", \"suspicious-looking\", \"sneaky\")","    .firstDescription(","        \"\"\"","        There is a suspicious-looking individual, holding a large bag,","        leaning against one wall. He is armed with a deadly stiletto.","        \"\"\"","    )","    .characterSheet(","        strength: 14,","        dexterity: 18,","        intelligence: 13,","        charisma: 7,","        bravery: 9,","        perception: 16,","        accuracy: 15,","        intimidation: 15,","        stealth: 17,","        level: 2,","        classification: .masculine,","        alignment: .neutralEvil","    )"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The NPC system is functional but basic. At this stage, complex dialogue trees or sophisticated AI behaviors would need custom implementation."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"What-about-combat-and-RPG-mechanics","text":"What about combat and RPG mechanics?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Melee combat exists but needs refinement. The Character Sheet system provides RPG stats but is underutilized.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Current support:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple turn-based attack mechanics"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Hit points and basic stats","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple weapon system"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is an area marked for improvement. If your game needs sophisticated combat, you may want to wait for future updates, or contribute improvements."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-mature-is-Gnusto","text":"How mature is Gnusto?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gnusto is in beta – stable enough for creating games but expect occasional API changes."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strengths:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Core engine is well-tested (80%+ test coverage)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Parser and world model are robust","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Auto-wiring eliminates most boilerplate","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Current limitations:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Documentation is still growing","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"No visual IDE or world builder","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Limited community resources"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some systems (combat, NPCs) need polish","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Can-I-contribute-or-get-help","text":"Can I contribute or get help?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes! We welcome questions, feedback, and contributions from the IF and open source communities."}]}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Questions & Issues","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto\/issues"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": PRs welcome (see CONTRIBUTING.md)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Community"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Growing! Early adopters shape the engine’s direction"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We especially value input from experienced IF authors on API design, missing features, and usability improvements."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Why-is-it-called-Gnusto","text":"Why is it called “Gnusto”?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"It’s an homage to Infocom’s Enchanter series, where “gnusto” copies magical spells into your spellbook.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Just as the spell preserves magic for reuse, the Gnusto engine aims to preserve and modernize the craft of interactive fiction. While the name has appeared in other IF tools historically, this project is unrelated to them."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Whats-the-development-philosophy","text":"What’s the development philosophy?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Gnusto balances respect for IF traditions with modern software engineering practices.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Core principles:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety First"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Type checking and structured state changes prevent common bugs"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Test Everything","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Games should be as testable as any other software"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Developer Experience"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Clear APIs, good error messages, and helpful tooling","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Honor the Past"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Respect IF conventions while enabling innovation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Development"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Community feedback shapes the engine’s evolution"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Whats-on-the-roadmap","text":"What’s on the roadmap?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The focus is on stabilizing the core engine, improving documentation, and building community."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Near term:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Stabilize save\/restore format"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Improve combat and NPC systems"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Expand documentation and tutorials"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create more example games"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Medium term:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Visual debugger\/inspector","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS and Android runtime","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Web-based play via WebAssembly","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"World builder tools"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Long term:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multimedia support","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced NPC\/dialogue systems"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Integration with AI for dynamic content","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Should-I-use-Gnusto-for-my-next-game","text":"Should I use Gnusto for my next game?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re comfortable with programming and want modern tooling for IF development, Gnusto is worth exploring."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Good fit if you:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Want type safety and IDE support"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enjoy test-driven development"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Need to integrate with other Swift libraries","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Prefer declarative, code-based authoring","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Want to contribute to a growing project","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Maybe wait if you:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefer visual tools or natural language authoring"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Need extensive multimedia support","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Want access to large existing libraries"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Require stable, unchanging APIs","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need comprehensive documentation\/tutorials"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Where-can-I-see-example-code","text":"Where can I see example code?","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The repository includes two example games that demonstrate best practices."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/Gnusto\/tree\/main\/Executables\/CloakOfDarkness"},{"text":": The standard IF demo, showing core concepts in ~200 lines","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/samadhiBot\/G